oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Scrapbook of Oscar Glaus of Nashville, Tennessee
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This World War, 1914-1918, scrapbook of Oscar Glaus, who had been a railroad clerk with NC & St.L, and served as a field supply clerk in World War, 1914-1918, contains numerous tickets, programs, clippings, lists, telegrams, aerial photos and letters. Glaus was stationed in Chaumont, France, for most of his miltary service.
